\"begin\": 535, \"end\": 540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Redwall\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.189162675594455e-16, \"text\": \"Arven\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Redwall\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Redwall\"}, {\"begin\": 541, \"end\": 550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcantara_(material)\", \"score\": 0.839243818964625, \"rank\": 0.050361240968968414, \"text\": \"Alcantara\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcantara_(material)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcantara_(material)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A win away from a second straight Olympic appearance, Barbosa absorbed a 2-0 loss to Kazakhstan's Samirkhon Ababakirov in the men's -58kg semifinals on Saturday, March 16.\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 787, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 701, \"end\": 711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9998782751687095, \"rank\": 8.08506292258916e-05, \"text\": \"Kazakhstan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barbosa struggled to score against the taller Kazakh, who utilized his length to keep the Filipino at bay and win convincingly by scores of 7-4, 16-5.\", \"from\": 789, \"to\": 939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 835, \"end\": 841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\", \"score\": 0.9971491228871654, \"rank\": 0.002784315184090949, \"text\": \"Kazakh\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only the top two athletes from each of the eight weight divisions - four for men and four for women - qualified for Paris.\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 1063, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1057, \"end\": 1062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999968508746, \"rank\": 3.1491012517673762e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mangin and Canabal also reached the semifinals but both ended up unsuccessful in their bids to make their Olympic debuts.\", \"from\": 1065, \"to\": 1186, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Canabal fell prey to Lebanon's Laetitia Aoun, 2-0, in the women's -57kg class on Saturday, while Mangin bowed to Saudi Arabia's Dunya Abutaleb, 2-0, in the women's -49 category on Friday.\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1375, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1209, \"end\": 1216, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lebanon_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999996995732541, \"rank\": 3.004169436248973e-07, \"text\": \"Lebanon\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lebanon_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lebanon_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1228, \"end\": 1232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michel_Aoun\", \"score\": 0.9982604206925981, \"rank\": 0.0017426107168733457, \"text\": \"Aoun\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michel_Aoun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michel_Aoun\"}, {\"begin\": 1307, \"end\": 1313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\", \"score\": 0.9998623444062681, \"rank\": 0.0001376744930128665, \"text\": \"Arabia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\"}, {\"begin\": 1316, \"end\": 1321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dunya\", \"score\": 0.7203681609941839, \"rank\": 0.38817906474354197, \"text\": \"Dunya\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dunya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dunya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mangin sustained arguably the closest loss among the three Filipino semifinalists as she fell to Abutaleb in a match that could have gone either way.\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1526, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A head kick gave Mangin a 3-0 lead in the opening round, but Abutaleb answered with a head kick of her own to forge a tie.\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1650, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two of the three officials then voted in favor of the Saudi Arabian in the tiebreaker.\", \"from\": 1651, \"to\": 1737, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1705, \"end\": 1710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\", \"score\": 0.9999811278963093, \"rank\": 1.1396156906333282e-05, \"text\": \"Saudi\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\"}, {\"begin\": 1711, \"end\": 1718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arab_world\", \"score\": 0.9677081719884907, \"rank\": 0.023028512267702465, \"text\": \"Arabian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arab_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arab_world\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Seeking to force a decider, Mangin kept in step with Abutaleb in the second round that went scoreless in the first 1:40 minutes until the Filipina incurred a gam-jeom (one-point penalty) with under 20 seconds remaining.\", \"from\": 1739, \"to\": 1958, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1877, \"end\": 1885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.9997825616195956, \"rank\": 0.00021748544192981678, \"text\": \"Filipina\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barbosa and Canabal, though, ended their campaigns on a high note as they won their bronze-medal matches against Saudi Arabia's Riad Hamdi and Cambodia's Julie Mam, respectively.\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 2138, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2079, \"end\": 2085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\", \"score\": 0.9998623444062681, \"rank\": 0.0001376744930128665, \"text\": \"Arabia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\"}, {\"begin\": 2093, \"end\": 2098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamdi_v._Rumsfeld\", \"score\": 0.9954646977258702, \"rank\": 0.0045559649522415166, \"text\": \"Hamdi\", \"types\": [\"Q2334719\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamdi_v._Rumsfeld\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamdi_v._Rumsfeld\"}, {\"begin\": 2103, \"end\": 2111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cambodia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9924597724317413, \"rank\": 0.007597483744022815, \"text\": \"Cambodia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cambodia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cambodia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2120, \"end\": 2123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mam_people\", \"score\": 0.9648631070301246, \"rank\": 0.036416454017088554, \"text\": \"Mam\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mam_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mam_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Alcantara exited the tournament following a 2-1 defeat at the hands of Ali Reza Abbasi of the Refugee Olympic Team in the men's -68kg quarterfinals.\", \"from\": 2140, \"to\": 2299, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2151, \"end\": 2160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcantara_(material)\", \"score\": 0.839243818964625, \"rank\": 0.050361240968968414, \"text\": \"Alcantara\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcantara_(material)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcantara_(material)\"}, {\"begin\": 2226, \"end\": 2237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reza_Abbasi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Reza Abbasi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reza_Abbasi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reza_Abbasi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will be the first time since the 2012 London Games that the Philippines will not be represented in Olympic taekwondo.\", \"from\": 2301, \"to\": 2421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2364, \"end\": 2375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7604207369815525, \"rank\": 0.31333079292276816, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barbosa donned the national colors in Tokyo in 2021, while retired Kirstie Alora saw action in the 2016 Rio de Janeiro Games.- Rappler.com  How does this make you feel?\", \"from\": 2423, \"to\": 2591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2461, \"end\": 2466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9619645179374903, \"rank\": 0.039539381413828616, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 2490, \"end\": 2503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kirstie_Alora\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kirstie Alora\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kirstie_Alora\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kirstie_Alora\"}, {\"begin\": 2550, \"end\": 2561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rappler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rappler.com\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q242